                <p class='bold'>Roommate/Housemate Assignments</p>
                <p>
                    You will be assigned roommates or housemates of your same gender and internship timeframe, and based on the profile you completed with Apple’s vendor, National Corporate Housing (NCH). Standard housing will be a shared bedroom and bathroom with one other person (traditional dorm style); graduate housing (master’s/MBA/PhD/JD) will be a shared two-bedroom unit with individual rooms; married couples/registered same-sex domestic partnership housing will be a one-bedroom/efficiency unit; and family housing will be a one-bedroom (with an infant) or two-bedroom (with a child) unit. Specific roommate/housemate requests cannot be guaranteed and we reserve the right to reassign you different roommates/housemates mid-internship if the need arises. If you have questions about your housing assignment, including gender identification–related concerns, please contact the Apple program manager.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Married couples/registered same-sex domestic partnership housing and family housing require the significant other and/or family to reside in corporate housing with the intern for the entire length of the internship. The significant other is required to pick up their key from the property management office separately.
                </p>
            </div>

