                <p class='bold'>Apartment Cleaning</p>
                <p>
                   Your apartment will be thoroughly cleaned, sanitized, and bedbug-free certified prior to your move-in date. You will be responsible for maintaining your apartment in good condition. This includes notifying NCH as soon as possible if you notice any leaks, mold, or other such issues. You may be charged for any damage and excessive cleaning fees after you move out. Failure to comply with scheduled cleaning, or failure to clean or remove trash from your room, may result in cleaning fees and/or your removal from corporate housing.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Biweekly maid service (light dusting, vacuuming, and bathroom and kitchen sanitizing) will be provided, and you will be notified of the housekeeping schedule upon arrival. NCH Housekeeping will not pick up or touch personal items that may prevent the team from completing the cleaning. Prior to the scheduled cleaning, floors and beds should be cleared to allow for proper vacuuming and linen changes. Do not mix personal linens (sheets, towels, pillow cases, and so on) with NCH linens. Apple University Relations will be notified if scheduled housekeeping cleanings are missed due to uncleared beds and floors or if excessive trash is not removed on a weekly basis. Additional cleaning fees may be equally charged to the intern residents if NCH Housekeeping is required to dispose of excessive trash.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Shared apartment units and bedrooms require diligent upkeep and cleaning between the biweekly housekeeping service, especially when new interns arrive; therefore, you are expected to keep your living quarters neat and tidy.
                </p>
            </div>

